THE 21-year-old matriculant who was raped on her way to write her exam is too traumatised to continue. The KZN Department of Education said the pupil, who was raped while on her way to write the first English paper last Tuesday, cannot continue writing her exams.She was allegedly walking alone when an unknown man threatened her with a knife. He dragged her into the bush and raped her. He then took her ID, textbooks and timetable.She managed to escape and ran to the police station.Education spokesman Kwazi Mthethwa said after the pupil was assessed it was discovered that she was too shocked and traumatised to be part of the exams.&ldquo;We have written to Umalusi and asked for the girl to be allowed to write her exams early next year. &ldquo;In the meantime we will continue providing her with counselling and hopefully it will help her,&rdquo; said Mthethwa.Umalusi spokesman Lucky Ditaunyane said the victim will be given an opportunity to write next year.&ldquo;We are aware of the incident. So yes, we will allow the victim to heal and use the opportunity early next year,&rdquo; said Ditaunyane.Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said no one has yet been arrested.